    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix SOR Transparent Container and ESM Message Container encoding length calculation\n\n### Summary\nThe encoding functions for SOR Transparent Container and ESM Message Container in the NAS layer were incorrectly calculating the length field values. This caused malformed NAS messages to be sent to the network, resulting in registration failures.\n\nThe issue was that the length field was being set to include the length field itself, rather than just the content length. Additionally, the buffer positioning for content encoding was incorrect, leading to data corruption in the encoded messages.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/NR_UE/5GS/5GMM/IES/SORTransparentContainer.c`: Fixed length calculation and buffer positioning in encoding function\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/EsmMessageContainer.c`: Applied identical fix for consistency\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Configure UE to perform registration with SOR support\n2. Observe that the SOR Transparent Container IE in registration messages has incorrect length field\n3. Network rejects registration due to malformed NAS message\n4. Similar issue occurs with ESM Container IEs during PDU session establishment\n\nThe fix ensures that length fields contain only the content length (excluding IEI and length octets) and that buffer positioning is correct for content encoding.\n"
}